data.type-tags#Type Tags:
By using type tags, you can use special numeric types that are not supported in the TypeScript.Just import Type (or typia.tags.Type) type, and combine it with number or bigint type through intersection symbol number & typia.tagsType<"float"> case. If you want to declare an union numeric type, combine | and bracket (()) symbols properly like below.When you take a mistake that choosing different target type, TypeScript compiler would block it with compilation error message. Therefore, have a confidence when using the Type tag. For such type safety reason, I recommend to use Type tag instead of using comment tags as much as possible.
number & (Type<"uint32"> | Type<"double">)
number type can be both uint32 and double
(number & Type<"int32">) | (bigint & Type<"uint64">)
number is int32
bigint is uint64
(number & (Type<"int32">)| Type<"float">) | (bigint & Type<"uint64">)
number can be both int32 and float
bigint is uint64
